# OpenShell gateway configuration overrides.
# Read by the openshell-gateway systemd --user service (EnvironmentFile).
# Symlinked into place by bootstrap/setup-host.sh:
#   ~/.config/openshell/gateway.env -> home-lab/openshell/gateway.env
#
# Contains NO secrets (driver + bind only) — committed despite the .gitignore
# *.env rule via an explicit exception. Do not put credentials here.

# Use the Docker compute driver (Docker Engine, rootful).
# All agent sandboxes (claude-code, NemoClaw's OpenClaw, future agents) run as
# Docker containers managed by the OpenShell gateway.
# Note: switching this from podman to docker orphans any existing Podman sandboxes;
# recreate them with `openshell sandbox create` after the driver change.
OPENSHELL_DRIVERS=docker

# REQUIRED: sandbox containers reach the gateway over the host bridge
# (host.docker.internal → bridge gateway IP), not loopback, so the gateway must
# not bind to 127.0.0.1. mTLS still gates every connection (client cert required).
# Cert SANs already include host.docker.internal, host.containers.internal, and 127.0.0.1.
OPENSHELL_BIND_ADDRESS=0.0.0.0
